{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox Academic Conference | logo = | discipline = [[Occupational safety and health]] | abbreviation = WAW | publisher = [[NRCWE]] | country = International | frequency = biannual (exception between 2016 and 2019) }} The International '''Wellbeing at Work''' ('''WAW''') series of academic conferences is relatively new in the field of [[occupational safety and health]]. WAW has been held biannually since 2010 and attracts researchers and practitioners of the field. In 2016, WAW 2016 was hosted by [https://www.tno.nl/en/ TNO] in Amsterdam <ref>{{Cite web|title = Home - Wellbeing at Work|url = http://www.wellbeingatwork.nl/|website = www.wellbeingatwork.nl|accessdate = 2015-10-24}}</ref> and in 2014, by [[The National Research Centre for the Working Environment|NRCWE]] in Copenhagenand .<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nrcwe.dk/waw2014|title=NRCWE: Projects: Wellbeing at Work 2014 in Copenhagen|website=nrcwe.dk|language=en|access-date=2018-02-16}}</ref> WAW 2012 was held in [[Manchester]], Great Brit.ain<ref>http://www.hsl.gov.uk/health-and-safety-conferences/wellbeing-2nd-international-conference-2012/home.aspx</ref> The next WAW (2019) will be hel in in Mau 2019Paris. The local organizer of this edition is INRS, the organization of this cycle of conferences is supported by the [http://www.perosh.eu/ PEROSH] "[http://www.perosh.eu/research-projects/perosh-projects/well-being-and-work/ Wellbeing and Work" project] group.
Perosh in the European Network for Research on Occupational Safety and Health. Wellbeing at work is considered a strategic component of OSH in Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.euro.who.int/en/health-topics/health-policy/health-2020-the-european-policy-for-health-and-well-being|title=Health 2020: the European policy for health and well-being|date=2018-02-16|website=www.euro.who.int|language=en|access-date=2018-02-16}}</ref>
